Setting up the User Name and user email & password
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
We can use this commands for Setup credentials


git config --global user.name "Enter your name"
git config --global user.email "Enter your Email"
git config --global user.Password "Enter your Password"

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


How to Remove the saved password & Credentials


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
We can use this commands for remove the saved credentials

git config --global --unset user.name
git config --global --unset user.email
git config --global --unset user.password

"You can use same commands for all replace the strings at the end"
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

How to Find the Configuration lists in git
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


We can use this command for finding conifiguration

git config --list

-------------------------------------------


Baiscs - Commands

--------------------------

git init -- We can use this command for intialzing the empty repository

git status -- We can use this command for tracking the file changes the file are tracked and untracked

git clone <Remote Repository URL> -- We can use this command for downlaoding & copying the whole repositiry in our local system from the remote repo

git add <filename> -- We can use this command for adding our files from workspace to  staging or index area

There are different type of file in our workspace so, if we want to add the all files at a time. We can use the below commands 

git add . (or) git add * (or) git add -A

git commit -m "type a sample message" -- we can use this commmand for "commiting our changes from staging area to local repo"

git push --- we can use this command for "pushing our changes from local to Remote repository"

git push origin --- Suppose if you have two branches if you want to push your changes into the specific branch you can use this below commands

    * git push origin <branch-name>
    
    * git push origin <specific barnch URL>

git log --> we can use this command for able to see the commit id's

git shoow --> we can use this command for see the files pushed

git branch -- we can see the list of branches in our workspace

git checkout <barnch name>--- we can navigate to the one branch to another branch for using this commaand

git checkbout -b <branch name> directly we can checkout into the branch with the help of this command






 
