 Linux Basic Commands for Creating Files

 ----------------------------------------------------------

 touch <fileName> --- we can use this command for creating the empty file

 touch {fileName,fileName2,..........,.....} ---- We can use this command for creating the multiple files

 Cat > <file name> --- We can use this command for creating file and write the content one time. After writing the text Press "ctrl + D"

 Cat >> >fileName> --- We can use this command for creating file and edit the content on the exisiting file. After writing the text Press "ctrl + D"
 
 Vi <fileName> ---- We can use this command for creating file and edit the content and delete the content and modify the content and you can see the content in vi editor


Vi editor stpes:

 * vi <fileName>

 *Press Esc button

 * Press "I" now you are in insert mode 

 * Now you can edit the content what ever you want!!

 * After that Press Escape button

 * Press "Shift"

 * Press Shift
  
 * Enter- :wq!

 * Click on enter

