Linux Basic Commands for Creating the Directories

--------------------------------------------------

mkdir <Name>-- we can use this command for creating the empty directory

mkdir d1/d2/d3 ---  we can use this command for creating the nested directory 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Linux Basic Commands for Removing the Directories and file

------------------------------------------------------------
rm <fileName>--removing the file

rm -rf <fileName>-- recursive force removing the file without any question

rmdir <DirName> -- we can use this command for deleting the directory

rm -rf <DirName> -- suppose if you have a files in your directory u can't delete the directory. so for that you can use this command deleting the directory directly without removing the files

